WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:05.800
Here is BharatDoc in a real doctor workflow.

00:05.800 --> 00:12.400
The doctor starts on the clinic dashboard, creates a new consultation, and enters a test Patient ID.

00:12.400 --> 00:18.600
Recording begins with one tap. The timer and online status make it clear that audio is captured locally first.

00:18.600 --> 00:24.800
When the consultation is finished, the doctor stops the recording. BharatDoc saves the audio on the device.

00:24.800 --> 00:31.400
The recording is sent for transcription and note generation, then opens as a consultation record.

00:31.400 --> 00:38.300
The doctor can review the transcript, generate a structured clinical summary, and check the draft.

00:38.300 --> 00:44.352
The goal is simple: keep the consultation natural, then turn it into documentation the doctor can verify.
